  "body": "Not all ReactTransitionGroup lifecycle hooks fire!  In the below examples, only \n\n'did appear'\n'will appear'\n\nlogs.  All of them should log.  I think this is a bug in React 15.\n\n``` javascript\nclass A extends Component {\n  constructor(props) {\n    super(props);\n  }\n  componentWillAppear(callback) {\n    callback();\n    console.log('will appear');\n  }\n\n  componentDidAppear() {\n    console.log('did appear');\n  }\n\n  componentWillEnter(callback) {\n    callback();\n    console.log('will enter');\n  }\n\n  componentDidEnter() {\n    console.log('did appear');\n  }\n\n  componentWillLeave(callback) {\n    callback();\n    console.log('will leave');\n  }\n\n  componentDidLeave() {\n    console.log('did appear');\n  }\n\n  render() {\n    return (\n      <div>HI</div>\n    );\n  }\n}\n\nclass A extends Component {\n  render() {\n    return (\n        <React.addons.TransitionGroup>\n          <B>\n          </B>\n        </React.addons.TransitionGroup>\n    );\n  }\n}\n```\n",
